libxr
------------------------------------------
Libxr is a library that allows for rapid implementation of RPC clients and
servers in C.

Libxr features:
 - Multiple RPC transports. (XML-RPC and JSON-RPC)
 - RPC interface description language (XDL)
 - Persistent connections over HTTP/1.1
 - Server session support for non-persistent connections
 - Multi-platform support (Linux, Windows, ...)
 - TLSv1 using GNUTLS

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.35-1
  libglib2.0-devel-2.42.1-2
  libglib2.0_0-2.42.1-2
  libjson-c-devel-0.11-2
  libxml2-2.9.2-1
  libxml2-devel-2.9.2-1
  libxr-devel-2.0.0-1bl2
  libxr2-2.0.0-1bl2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-1
  cygport-0.18.1-1
  gcc-core-4.9.2-3
  libtool-2.4.6-1
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/megous/libxr

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/megous/libxr/archive/2.0.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libxr-2.0.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libxr-2.0.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libxr-2.0.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libxr-2.0.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libxr2-2.0.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libxr-devel-2.0.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libxr)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libxr.README
  /usr/share/doc/libxr/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/libxr/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libxr/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/libxr/README

(libxr2)
  /usr/bin/cygxr-2.dll

(libxr-devel)
  /usr/bin/xdl-compiler.exe
  /usr/include/libxr/xr-call.h
  /usr/include/libxr/xr-client.h
  /usr/include/libxr/xr-config.h
  /usr/include/libxr/xr-http.h
  /usr/include/libxr/xr-lib.h
  /usr/include/libxr/xr-server.h
  /usr/include/libxr/xr-value-utils.h
  /usr/include/libxr/xr-value.h
  /usr/lib/libxr.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libxr.pc
  /usr/share/man/man1/xdl-compiler.1.gz

